 and orange zest in mixing bowl. Arrange quince in Varoma dish, set Varoma in position and steam <b>17-22 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b> or until tender, adjusting steaming time according to size and ripeness of quince. Meanwhile, remove prebaked logs of biscotti from oven (they should feel soft to touch) and allow to cool for 10 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 150°C. Set Varoma aside."},{"content":"Remove lemon peelings, orange peelings and cardamom pods from syrup. Place quince into a container (1 litre) then pour in cardamom syrup. Cover and refrigerate for 2-3 hours."},{"content":"Using a sharp knife, slice biscotti dough (approx. 1 cm thick). Place slices back onto prepared baking tray and bake for a further 25-35 minutes (150°C). Allow to cool completely before storing in an airtight container."},{"content":"When ready to serve, remove cardamom syrup container from fridge, pour syrup into mixing bowl and, without measuring cup, reduce <b>8-12 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b> or until slightly thickened (it will thicken more as it cools). Serve poached quince with 1-2 Tbsp of cardamom syrup and a biscotti."}],"hintsAndTricks":["For a more intense flavour, store the poached quince for <b>1-2 days<b> before serving.","Store quince in the fridge in a jar filled with syrup for up to one month."],"basicInfo":["medium","55m","1h 50m","8 portions"]}